  BOOKS: [
    {
      id: "players_guide",
      title: "B&B Player's Guide",
      subtitle: "Core Rules & Character Creation",
      cover: "assets/players_guide.png",
      chapters: [
        {
          title: "Chapter 1: The Frontier Call",
          content: `<p>Welcome to <strong>Beasts & Bounties (B&B)</strong>, a dark fantasy tabletop roleplaying game. In this world, civil kingdoms exist only as walled islands in a vast, terrifying frontier infested with ancient creatures, rogue spellcasters, and legendary beasts. You play as a Hunter"”a member of the Guild, contracted to enter the wilderness and complete bounties.</p>
          <h3>Core Attributes</h3>
          <p>Unlike other fantasy systems, B&B defines characters using six attributes representing their training, physical limits, and general fortune:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Strength (Str):</strong> Power, lifting ability, and physical force.</li>
            <li><strong>Dexterity (Dex):</strong> Reflexes, speed, and subtle hand gestures.</li>
            <li><strong>Constitution (Con):</strong> Health, endurance, and toxicity resistance.</li>
            <li><strong>Intelligence (Int):</strong> Deduction, magical theory, and ancient languages.</li>
            <li><strong>Wisdom (Wis):</strong> Survival instinct, sensory awareness, and medicine.</li>
            <li><strong>Luck (Lck):</strong> Your favor with the fates, impacting trade, charisma, and sudden strokes of fortune.</li>
          </ul>`
        },
        {
          title: "Chapter 2: Resource Pools",
          content: `<p>Hunters rely on three vital resources to survive combat and explore the frontier:</p>
          <h3>Hit Points (HP)</h3>
          <p>Your physical health. If HP reaches 0, you collapse and must make Death Saves (requiring 3 successes before 3 failures to stabilize).</p>
          <h3>Mana Points (MP)</h3>
          <p>Occult energy used to manifest spells, trigger runic weapons, and cast wards. Recouped on long rests.</p>
          <h3>Stamina Points (SP)</h3>
          <p>Physical energy spent on weapon techniques, athletic feats, and quick reflexes. Some recovered on short rests.</p>`
        }
      ]
    }
],
